explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the counts of each atom. It iterates over the formula string, and whenever it encounters a '(', it pushes a new dictionary onto the stack. Whenever it encounters a ')', it pops the dictionary from the stack and multiplies the count of each atom by the count of the current group. Finally, it constructs the result string by iterating over the atoms in the last dictionary in sorted order.

